# Corva Data Reference

When writing code that interacts with the Corva platform, consult `corva_data_dictionary.md` for field-level details.

## Key Files

- `corva_data_dictionary.md` — Full data dictionary (102 datasets, 3500+ fields, organized by category)
- `corva_data_dictionary.csv` — Same data in CSV format (source of truth for human edits)
- `corva_datasets_catalog.csv` — All 647 datasets (summary-level, no field details)

## Corva API Pattern

```
GET /api/v1/data/{provider}/{dataset}/
```

Query parameters: `query` (MongoDB JSON), `sort`, `limit`, `skip`, `fields`

Dataset names use `provider#collection` format (e.g., `corva#wits`).
In API paths, the `#` becomes `/`: `/api/v1/data/corva/wits/`

## Data Types

- `time` — queried by `timestamp` + `asset_id`
- `depth` — queried by `measured_depth` + `asset_id`
- `reference` — configuration data, not time-series

